=== devFluid Twitter Puller Robot ===

== How to Install & Run ==

git clone https://github.com/satsukitv/devfluid-twitter-puller.git
npm install

Run robots.sql to create table to store data. Modify structure as needed.
Create a mySQL user for the twitter robot.
Create a developer profile, an app with a consumer key and secret.
Get the access token and secret for the user you want to read tweets from.
Edit config.js.dist to include all these keys, and rename to config.js.

node twitter_puller.js